In Rodrigo Duterte’s Philippines, a Tale of Two Rallies Rival rallies reveal an increasingly polarized nation in the wake of Duterte’s war on drugs By Google+ Feb. 26, 2017 1:25 a.m. ET 
Tensions deepened in the Philippines this weekend after the country’s justice secretary asked tens of thousands of President Rodrigo Duterte’s supporters who else they would like to see locked up after police arrested a prominent antigovernment senator on Friday. 
“Who do you want next?” Vitaliano Aguirre II asked a huge crowd who gathered overnight on Saturday in support of Mr. Duterte and his bloody war on drugs.
